column1: Since 2017 I have been standing tall for #NorthFlorida. I am fighting for a clean #environment a livable wage affordable healthcare resources for our #veterans quality #education & more. #Vote on August 18 for #Lawson4Congress in #FL05. #covid19 #WomensRights  #smallbusiness https://t.co/55dUJTbqA6

America is suffering from two pandemics: #COVID-19 health crisis & one that's plagued us for centuries — racism. Join me @AttorneyCrump & other community advocates for "Say Their Names: A Conversation on Racial Injustice" Monday Aug 10 at 6PM #FL05 #SayTheirNames #Flapol #BLM https://t.co/ZMHSp5C6nH
Join the Minority Small Business Roundtable conversation as we discuss small businesses impacted by COVID-19. Watch here ==> https://t.co/UbZik3xjE7

Join us today at the grand opening of our #Tallahassee campaign office from 12-4PM. Our office is located at 412 W. Tenn Street (Bethel Plaza).   Reminder: In an effort to mitigate the spread of COVID-19 please follow @LeonCounty guidelines & #WearAMask. #FL05 #Lawson4Congress https://t.co/BCMMoVBZib

It’s official I filed my qualifying paperwork for re-election this afternoon. Looking forward to running a great campaign but more than that - continuing to help our families businesses veterans and seniors overcome the impact of Covid-19. We have more work to do! #FlaPol https://t.co/8KX6VGFmFx

#COVID19 is causing a staggering impact on the #BlackCommunity. Why?  Limited access to health care💉 Crowded living conditions🏘 Lack of resources📚💰 Food desserts🚫🍎🥗  It's critical we address why our community is disproportionately suffering #FL05 https://t.co/x9LoC4zNnc

#Floridians are experiencing financial uncertainty due to #COVID19. I urged the #FLGov to increase the state's unemployment payout $600/week waive the job search requirements and extend the time workers are eligible for unemployment to 26 weeks. #FL05  https://t.co/dJiDWPYJcJ

How can we ask residents to wash their hands to stop the spread of the #coronavirus but companies are still shutting off their water? Americans need access to clean water. #Florida should temporarily suspend the disconnection of water sewer and gas during the #COVID19 pandemic. https://t.co/2N9PftM66g

The #Coronavirus #stimuluspackage provides monetary payments protections for renters & homeowners help for the unemployed benefits for student loan borrowers & support for small businesses. I'm monitoring the situation & fighting to deliver more relief https://t.co/bH5rFO5gR9
